<paragraph blockId="10.[1404,2608,2488,3460]" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">
Possibly it is native only to 
<collectingRegion box="[1766,1826,2601,2634]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">Java</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1897,1949,2601,2634]" country="Indonesia" name="Bali" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">Bali</collectingRegion>
islands, introduced into Lombok, 
<collectingCountry box="[2434,2520,2601,2634]" name="Indonesia" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">Flores</collectingCountry>
, Sumbawa, Sumba, Timor, 
<collectingRegion box="[1720,1838,2649,2674]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
, and Moluccan Islands in ancient times. It was introduced during the last centuries in many locations, including New 
<collectingCountry box="[2321,2424,2688,2713]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, Aru Islands, New Britain Is, 
<collectingCountry box="[1630,1756,2728,2753]" name="Australia" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1776,1965,2728,2753]" name="New Zealand" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1985,2203,2728,2753]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[2224,2359,2728,2753]" name="Mauritius" pageId="10" pageNumber="417">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, and Comoro Is. The map represents the native range and the oldest introductions.
</paragraph>
